The paper deals with coding theory and optimization, which are both relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The use of matrices and linear programming also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses soft decoding techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and signal processing (cs.SI), and the use of efficient algorithms, which is relevant to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
